==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cassareep
<hw>Cas"sa*reep</hw> <pr>(k⟦acr⟧s"s⟦adot⟧*r⟦emac⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<def>A condiment made from the sap of the bitter cassava (<spn>Manihot
utilissima</spn>) deprived of its poisonous qualities, concentrated by
boiling, and flavored with aromatics. See <er>Pepper pot</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cassate</ent>⟦br⟧
